WEBVTT

00:01.125 --> 00:07.125
♪

00:08.750 --> 00:12.000
WOMAN:
<i>Of course, I do understand...</i>

00:12.000 --> 00:13.959
Hey, uh, Mom, Dad,
have you seen my phone?

00:13.959 --> 00:16.083
Oh, oh, oh! Oh, no.
What are you doing?

00:16.083 --> 00:17.458
Well, we have to do it this way

00:17.458 --> 00:19.458
so we can both watch
<i>Charlie Rose.</i>

00:19.458 --> 00:21.208
MATT: Okay, I'm sorr--
JOAN: This is why I keep

00:21.208 --> 00:23.875
saying--
move back into your bedroom.

00:23.875 --> 00:25.333
Don't live in the damn garage.

00:25.333 --> 00:26.750
MATT: Yeah, and I keep
saying to you, Mother,

00:26.750 --> 00:29.000
that feels really permanent and
I need this to be a temporary--

00:29.000 --> 00:30.583
You know what, I can't have
this conversation with you.

00:30.583 --> 00:31.709
There's too many holes
in that afghan.

00:31.709 --> 00:32.792
-Just...
-Here, I found it.

00:32.792 --> 00:34.333
-Keep it.
-It was under your mother.

00:34.333 --> 00:36.250
JOAN: Oh, honey.

00:36.250 --> 00:39.041
♪

00:39.041 --> 00:40.709
Sit down, your mother
made you a waffle.

00:40.709 --> 00:42.000
Oh, no, no.

00:42.000 --> 00:45.083
I am not having
the special-talk waffles.

00:45.083 --> 00:47.792
Now, if you'll please excuse me,

00:47.792 --> 00:49.333
I am going to go buy
a new phone.

00:49.333 --> 00:50.458
JOHN: Yeah, you should.

00:50.458 --> 00:51.750
It accidentally filmed us,

00:51.750 --> 00:53.583
and I don't know
how to delete it.

00:53.583 --> 00:56.834
-Oh!
-Oh, God.

00:56.834 --> 00:57.750
Honey.

00:57.750 --> 00:59.709
Honey, having
you back home,

00:59.709 --> 01:01.542
it's a big adjustment
for all of us.

01:01.542 --> 01:04.750
I'm now a porn star, I didn't--

01:04.750 --> 01:06.625
That's--it filmed us.

01:06.625 --> 01:09.041
-You can delete that.
-I'd give it up, Joanie.

01:09.041 --> 01:11.333
He doesn't want to talk to his
mom about<i> it.</i>

01:11.333 --> 01:12.333
That's true, I don't.

01:12.333 --> 01:14.083
You may not want
to talk to your mom about it,

01:14.083 --> 01:17.792
but you should at least
talk to a therapist.

01:17.792 --> 01:19.083
Oh, man.

01:19.083 --> 01:21.333
I mean, of course I didn't want
to see my parents doing that,

01:21.333 --> 01:23.208
but I just--I don't see
how talking about this

01:23.208 --> 01:24.500
is gonna make it go away.

01:24.500 --> 01:27.625
Well, then, is there a feeling
that you wish would go away?

01:27.625 --> 01:29.333
There's an image
I wish would go away.

01:29.333 --> 01:32.083
Right, but you need to talk
about this with someone.

01:32.083 --> 01:33.458
-I talked about it.
-You did?

01:33.458 --> 01:35.041
Yeah, with Greg and Heather,
I texted all night.

01:35.041 --> 01:37.166
Believe me, they're just
as disturbed as I am.

01:37.166 --> 01:39.625
Oh.

01:39.625 --> 01:41.875
That's so interesting.

01:41.875 --> 01:44.834
You know, I think
it's clear that, as a family,

01:44.834 --> 01:46.667
we're falling
into some unhealthy

01:46.667 --> 01:48.458
communication patterns.

01:48.458 --> 01:51.542
If we can send it electronically
through our phones

01:51.542 --> 01:56.959
then we can say it emotionally
through our mouths.

01:56.959 --> 01:58.208
-Yes?
-I was told

01:58.208 --> 01:59.375
there would be doughnuts.

01:59.375 --> 02:01.291
-Yeah, they're coming.
-Do we really have to

02:01.291 --> 02:04.000
be here all just because
Matt walked in on

02:04.000 --> 02:05.709
whatever it is
he walked in on?

02:05.709 --> 02:07.458
Greg, you can't even say it.

02:07.458 --> 02:09.333
-Intercourse.
-Oh, you're such a kiss-ass.

02:09.333 --> 02:11.083
HEATHER: The sooner
we give her what she wants,

02:11.083 --> 02:12.166
the sooner
this is over.

02:12.166 --> 02:13.583
Amen to that, girl.

02:13.583 --> 02:15.625
JEN: Yeah, you're
buying me a new purse.

02:15.625 --> 02:17.709
-Sure.
-Have you given any thought

02:17.709 --> 02:19.333
to what you would say to a child

02:19.333 --> 02:21.250
who saw you
in that situation?

02:21.250 --> 02:24.000
GREG: Our baby only sees shapes
and colors right now, Mom,

02:24.000 --> 02:25.625
so I think it would
really just be guesswork.

02:25.625 --> 02:27.625
-Yeah.
-Okay, okay.

02:27.625 --> 02:29.875
The real issue here
is communication,

02:29.875 --> 02:34.083
and that affects every member
of this family.

02:34.083 --> 02:36.041
Why did we
have to get out of the pool?

02:36.041 --> 02:37.583
Because Uncle Matt walked in

02:37.583 --> 02:39.959
on Mom-Mom and Pop-Pop
communicating.

02:39.959 --> 02:41.375
-Dude.
-Oh, dude.

02:41.375 --> 02:43.000
-Dude.
-So...

02:43.000 --> 02:45.291
Can we go back
to playing Marco Polo?

02:45.291 --> 02:47.583
Yes, but first I have a game

02:47.583 --> 02:50.208
that might be even more fun.

02:50.208 --> 02:53.417
Can you do your job
overseas?

02:53.417 --> 02:55.250
Okay, everybody,

02:55.250 --> 02:58.542
keep eye contact
and be honest.

02:58.542 --> 02:59.750
Like this:

02:59.750 --> 03:02.500
John, sometimes
I feel I need you

03:02.500 --> 03:04.000
to be more
in the moment.

03:04.000 --> 03:07.333
JOHN: Um, keeping it fresh...

03:07.333 --> 03:08.583
keeps it special.

03:08.583 --> 03:10.166
Oh, thank you.

03:10.166 --> 03:12.417
He just read that
off the doughnut box.

03:12.417 --> 03:14.667
JOHN: Well, yeah, but
I read it in the moment.

03:14.667 --> 03:17.000
JOAN: Ready, set--

03:17.000 --> 03:19.125
keep sharing,
keep looking--

03:19.125 --> 03:20.583
go!

03:20.583 --> 03:22.542
I've always been
intimidated by your strength.

03:22.542 --> 03:25.417
Yeah, I'm not doing this.

03:25.417 --> 03:26.750
That was strong.

03:26.750 --> 03:28.166
You need to start
wearing deodorant.

03:28.166 --> 03:30.333
I know what you do
in the bathroom.

03:30.333 --> 03:31.417
GREG: So, who did
you see more of,

03:31.417 --> 03:33.709
-Mom or Dad?
-Dude.

03:33.709 --> 03:36.125
It was like watching two
candles melt onto each other.

03:36.125 --> 03:37.750
-Oh.
-Yeah.

03:37.750 --> 03:40.834
-You promise to be honest?
-100%.

03:40.834 --> 03:43.208
Who's your favorite child?

03:43.208 --> 03:44.458
Tim.

03:44.458 --> 03:46.625
-Pretty sure it's Tyler.
-Ugh.

03:46.625 --> 03:50.500
